Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Peel @garlic{2%clove}; finely chop half and leave remaining whole. Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Thinly slice @chives{¼%ounce}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

== Crème Fraîche Mashed Potatoes ==

Place potatoes and whole garlic in a medium #pot with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until potatoes are tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to #pot.

Mash with @crème fraîche{2%tablespoon} and @butter{1%tablespoon} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Roasted Broccoli ==

While potatoes cook, toss broccoli on a #baking sheet with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, a pinch of @chili flakes{1%teaspoon}, and @salt{}.

Roast on middle rack until tender and lightly browned, ~{15-20%minutes}.

== Pan-Seared Scallops ==

Meanwhile, pat @jumbo sea scallops{8%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with half the @smoked paprika{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a large, preferably nonstick, #pan over medium-high heat. Add scallops and cook until opaque and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate. Tent with #foil to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

== Lemon Butter Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in same #pan over medium heat. Add chopped garlic and half the lemon zest. Cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @seafood stock concentrate{1}, a big squeeze of lemon juice, and @water{¼%cup}. Simmer until slightly reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} and half the chives.

== To Serve ==

Divide scallops, mashed potatoes, and broccoli between plates. Top scallops with sauce. Garnish dish with remaining chives. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Scallops are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145º.